Comment (src/components/catalogs/ControlCreateForm.vue:87):
**[Medium] Server error detail is dropped here â€” inconsistent with the sibling forms.**

This `getErrorMessage` only reads `error.message`, so when the API rejects a control (e.g. duplicate ID, validation failure) the user sees axios's generic `Request failed with status code 4xx` instead of the server's message. `GroupCreateForm.vue` and `CatalogEditModal.vue` in this same PR correctly extract `errorResponse.response?.data.errors?.body` first.

Suggest mirroring the group form:

```ts
function getErrorMessage(error: unknown): string {
  const errorResponse = error as AxiosError<ErrorResponse<ErrorBody>>;
  return (
    errorResponse.response?.data?.errors?.body ||
    (error instanceof Error ? error.message : 'Failed to create control.')
  );
}
```
Replies:
**lisa implementation guidance:** In `src/components/catalogs/ControlCreateForm.vue`, update `getErrorMessage` to match the sibling create/edit forms by extracting `errorResponse.response?.data?.errors?.body` before falling back to `error.message` or `Failed to create control.`. Add the needed type imports for `AxiosError`, `ErrorResponse`, and `ErrorBody`. Keep the three existing submit paths in `createControl` unchanged and do not add payload trimming, ID normalization, or endpoint changes.

