Comment (src/components/catalogs/CatalogEditModal.vue:30):
**[Medium] Stale error/validation state survives closing and reopening the dialog.**

`errors` and `errorMessage` live in this component, which stays mounted in the parent view â€” only the Dialog's *content* is unmounted on hide. So: submit with an empty title (or hit a server error), Cancel, reopen â†’ the old error banner and field errors are still displayed, since they're only cleared on the next `validate()` call.

This applies to all five edit modals in this PR (`CatalogEditModal`, `ControlEditModal`, `GroupEditModal`, `ControlPartEditModal`, `GroupDescriptionModal`). The create forms are fine because they live inside the Dialog slot and remount fresh.

Suggest resetting on open, e.g.:

```ts
watch(show, (open) => {
  if (open) {
    Object.keys(errors).forEach((key) => delete errors[key]);
    errorMessage.value = '';
  }
});
```
